    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-25T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-25T02:00:00-05:00" n="66"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d66">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115 Radio Corporation of America/1½:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1"
                            type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-25T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 25, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 25—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have been informed by local representative of Radio Corporation of America that
                    he has received information from an American source, undivulged, which he
                    considers reliable, that the Japanese intend to occupy the radio transmitting
                    station at Chenju, 7 miles from Shanghai, at 8 o’clock tonight. He states that
                    the Radio Corporation of America has a substantial financial interest in this
                    station and he desires all steps to be taken which will prevent the station
                    being closed. I have told him that in the event he secured confirmation of this
                    intention I will inform the Japanese Consul General of the American interest in
                    the plant and endeavor to ascertain the intentions of the Japanese there [<hi
                        rend="italic">military?</hi>].</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
